<p>I'm looking for some manner of workaround for a problem I'm having with views that include spatial relation clauses, specifically on 5.5.41-MariaDB. If not a workaround, then at least a confirmation that this kind of clause is unsupported in views. On to examples!</p>  <p>This select statement works </p>  <pre><code>SELECT m.*  FROM members m  INNER JOIN ipDB ON Intersects(ipDB.ip_range, Polygon( LineString( Point(INET_ATON(m.signup_ip), 1), Point(INET_ATON(m.signup_ip), 0), Point(INET_ATON(m.signup_ip) + 0.5, 0), Point(INET_ATON(m.signup_ip) + 0.5, 1), Point(INET_ATON(m.signup_ip), 1)))) WHERE ipDB.name LIKE '%special%'; </code></pre>  <p>This create view works, too</p>  <pre><code>CREATE VIEW debug_view AS (  SELECT m.*   FROM members m   INNER JOIN ipDB ON Intersects(ipDB.ip_range, Polygon( LineString( Point(INET_ATON(m.signup_ip), 1), Point(INET_ATON(m.signup_ip), 0), Point(INET_ATON(m.signup_ip) + 0.5, 0), Point(INET_ATON(m.signup_ip) + 0.5, 1), Point(INET_ATON(m.signup_ip), 1))))  WHERE ipDB.name LIKE '%special%'; ) </code></pre>  <p>However, this select of the view</p>  <pre><code>SELECT * FROM debug_view; </code></pre>  <p>Triggers this error:</p>  <pre><code>Error in query (1356): View 'debug_view' references invalid table(s) or column(s) or function(s) or definer/invoker of view lack rights to use them </code></pre>  <p>Any thoughts?</p>